# Use Cloudflare Agents as ShitRat Control Plane

## Decision

Use Cloudflare Agents SDK as the primary runtime/control plane for ShitRat's Slack presence.

## Why

Cloudflare Agents gives ShitRat a durable named instance, persistent state, WebSocket/RPC surfaces, scheduling, queues, and Workflow integration. That maps well to a familiar that needs to remember state, react to Slack events, and report progress without depending on a terminal session staying open.

## Boundary

Cloudflare does not directly own private local machine capabilities. Local pi, repo work, filesystem access, and machine actions stay behind signed private executor ingress. The executor/router boundary must stay replaceable without changing the Slack control plane.

## Consequence

The first repo slice should prove Slack event ingress, Durable Object state/dedupe, signed executor bridge dispatch, and threaded Slack result reporting. Cloudflare should not call private executor hosts directly; all privileged local work should route through one signed choke point. Flue remains a candidate harness behind that executor boundary for future agent sessions.
